  "A spotlight on the ground is 20 m from a wall. A person 2 m tall walks toward the wall at 1 m/s. How fast is the length of their shadow on the wall changing when they are 10 m from the wall?": "",
  "The shadow is shrinking at 1 m/s": "",
  "The shadow is shrinking at 2 m/s": "",
  "The shadow is growing at 0.4 m/s": "",
  "The shadow is shrinking at 0.4 m/s": "",
  "By similar triangles: s/20 = 2/x where x is distance from spotlight. s = 40/x. ds/dt = -40/x^2 * dx/dt. Person is 10m from wall, so x = 10. dx/dt = -1 (approaching wall). ds/dt = -40/100 * (-1) = 0.4... Wait: the person walks toward the wall, so away from the spotlight means x increases. At 10m from wall, x = 10 from the light? Actually x = distance from light = 20-10 = 10m from light. ds/dt = -40/100*1 = -0.4 m/s.": ""
